column1: # Total for 1820 omitted as monthly readings for the year are incomplete.
# The December 1826 reading is shown in brackets on the sheet without explanation. It has been retained.
# The May 1863 reading and 1863 total are shown in brackets on the sheet without explanation. They have been retained.
# November 1864 figure of 7.28 is queried in a note on the sheet, suggesting it should be 2.28.
# January-February 1865 are grouped into a single aggregate reading of 6.00 on the sheet.
# Total for 1866 (shown in brackets) omitted as monthly readings for the year are incomplete.
# Total for 1867 (shown in brackets) omitted as there are no monthly readings for the year, so this is likely to be an estimate from other sites.
# Total for 1871 (shown in brackets) omitted as there are no monthly readings for the year, so this is likely to be an estimate from other sites.
# October 1872 figure is identified as part-estimate on the sheet and has been retained.
# Totals for 1873 and 1878 (shown in brackets) omitted as monthly readings for the years are incomplete, so they are likely to be an estimates from other sites.
# Totals for 1884 and 1888 are shown in brackets because of small gauge moves during the years, and have been retained.
# January-April 1894 grouped aggregate reading of 7.50 omitted as there were no observations and this is an estimate from other sites.
# Directions on sheet put the site at the Rectory.
